$ R function: colorRampPalette

`colorRampPalette` returns a → development/languages/R/function[function].
The function can then be called with a positive integer argument `n` and the function will return a → development/languages/R/graphics/coloring/palettes with `n` entries.
code {
paletteFunc <- colorRampPalette(…); # Create function
palette     <- paletteFunc(8);      # invoke function to create a palette with eight entries.
code }

{ Create a palette from red to blue

  The following example creates a palette from red to blue with 8 entries and uses → development/languages/R/functions/barplot[`barplot`] to display these:

